1Ô∏è‚É£ What is FPGA?

Full Form

FPGA = Field-Programmable Gate Array

‚∏ª

Simple Definition

An FPGA is a hardware chip that can be programmed after manufacturing to perform custom digital logic functions.

Unlike CPUs (fixed function) or ASICs (fixed design), FPGA is reconfigurable.

‚∏ª

Plain English

üëâ FPGA = Hardware that you can ‚Äúre-wire‚Äù using software.

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ Real-Life Analogy üß±

Think of FPGA like LEGO blocks.
	‚Ä¢	You can build a car today
	‚Ä¢	Break it
	‚Ä¢	Build a plane tomorrow

Same chip ‚Äî different hardware logic.

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ Why FPGA Exists

Before FPGAs:
	‚Ä¢	Custom hardware required ASIC manufacturing
	‚Ä¢	ASIC design costs millions
	‚Ä¢	Changes impossible after fabrication

FPGA solves this by allowing:

‚úî Rapid prototyping
‚úî Hardware testing
‚úî Design flexibility
‚úî Firmware upgrades

‚∏ª

4Ô∏è‚É£ FPGA vs CPU vs ASIC vs CPLD

Feature	FPGA	ASIC	CPU	CPLD
Programmable	‚úÖ	‚ùå	Software only	Limited
Performance	High	Very high	Moderate	Low
Flexibility	Very high	None	High (software)	Moderate
Cost	Medium	Very high	Medium	Low


